##Hundreds of retired doctors and nurses return to the front line in Ezhou

Since the outbreak of the new crown pneumonia, it has affected the surrounding cities of Wuhan, and Ezhou is no exception.

According to the map, Ezhou is "surrounded" by Wuhan, Huanggang and Huangshi. With an area of only 1,594 square kilometers, it is the smallest prefecture-level city in Hubei Province. However, Wuhan and Huanggang are the two areas with the most severe epidemic in Hubei, the situation in Ezhou is also critical.

As of 2400 hours on February 8, Ezhou had reported 639 new cases of pneumonia, 227 suspected cases and 21 deaths, according to the official Ezhou City Government website.

As of 2400 hours on February 8, New Ezhou was the province's fourth-largest confirmed case of pneumonia, with a case fatality rate of 3.29 percent, according to the provincial health commission in official website. Ezhou's "war epidemic" in the face of the problem is the lack of medical protection and the number of medical staff, some suspected of new crown pneumonia patients, but also because the hospital has no beds can not be admitted.

Under the epidemic, strengthen travel control, set up a focus on the point of view, the provincial medical team, called for retired medical staff to return to work... the Ezhou City Government introduced a number of measures, with central and local support, fixed-point hospital receives and treats the patient with all one's strength, strengthens the epidemic situation prevention and control dynamics. From the official to the civilian, from the urban to the rural, a "war epidemic" started in Ezhou. As of 2400 hours on February 8, a total of 42 patients had been discharged from hospitals in Ezhou.

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
A group of patients and medical staff pose for a photograph after 22 patients were discharged from hospital in Ezhou on February 8,2010. Photograph: Ezhou City Hall

APPEAL FOR DONATIONS: Phone calls for donations of medical supplies are made daily

As early as the end of January, the "war epidemic" in Ezhou sounded the alarm.

From January 24 to January 25, Ezhou Central Hospital, Ezhou Second Hospital, Ezhou Third Hospital, Ezhou Maternal and Child Health Hospital and Ezhou Hospital of Traditional Chinese Medicine announced that in order to better treat patients and protect medical personnel, will receive outside donations of medical supplies.

Over the past few days, a reporter from the Beijing News has called several hospitals in Ezhou, all of which have been told they still accept donations of medical supplies. Ms. Jiang, who is in charge of procurement at Ezhou Central Hospital, said it had been difficult to procure recently. Many factories have not resumed production, and many cities are now under siege, with workers unable or unwilling to return. After the purchase of materials, logistics has become a problem, at present can only through the postal delivery, or by the supplier sent.

More than 1,700 medical staff at the hospital consume about 3,000 N95 masks a day, leaving just one more day in stock, said Ms. Liu, who is in charge of receiving donations. Protective clothing daily consumption of about 3000 pieces, disposable medical masks daily consumption of about 6000. "medical masks are the most scarce item, and 75 per cent of alcohol is also scarce. "

On February 8, a staff member at Ezhou II hospital said the hospital was short of protective clothing for just two or three days and had a relatively comfortable supply of masks. "when we are nervous, we will use them with KF94 masks, " a staff member said

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
Ezhou General Hospital Announces Acceptance of donations.

At present, Ezhou hospitals lack N95 masks, protective clothing and body heat guns, said a staff member in charge of receiving supplies at Ezhou's new crown pneumonia command. The headquarters has received a lot of donations, but it is hoped that the community will continue to donate, "because the prevention and control of the epidemic may be a protracted war. ".

After the announcement of the receipt of donations, all parties in the community have responded.

"It's a pity, " said a staff member at Ezhou Central Hospital, which receives many supplies these days, though some are not for medical use and are therefore not available, ms. Liu, who is in charge of receiving donated materials at the hospital, said in a friend circle that over the past 10 days, she has added more than 800 wechat signals and hundreds of groups. The phone calls are answered almost 24 hours a day without interruption, and then she goes to the warehouse at any time to receive, count and move goods.

"I am very tired, but my heart is very warm, " she wrote on her facebook page. "thank you from all over the world for your concern and care for Ezhou Central Hospital. We will beat you with new pneumonia. "

Medical Emergency: Retired medical workers return to the front line to help Ezhou

Ezhou is in need not only of medical supplies, but also of medical staff.

On February 4, the Ezhou Government issued an initiative, saying that at that time, Ezhou had the second highest infection rate and fatality rate of new crown pneumonia in the province, with 3,681 Ezhou Medical personnel and 137 Guizhou Medical Team members already involved in the "war epidemic" , but Ezhou remains the most under-pressure in the province and the country, especially with the most acute shortage of staff with first-line experience in infectious diseases.

Lin Bin, a Ezhou resident, said that Ezhou is close to Wuhan, and that when local residents get sick, most of them go to Wuhan hospitals. He is also used to taking his children to Wuhan for medical treatment. In his view, Ezhou is not rich in local medical resources, although there are six larger hospitals, there are three-tier hospitals, "but medical resources and Wuhan can not be compared. ".

Several medical staff at Ezhou Central Hospital and Ezhou Second Hospital told the Beijing News that they had been working overtime for several days in an effort to treat patients with new pneumonia. Even so, the medical staff was still under strain.

In the document, the Ezhou City Government called on retired and former health care workers and individual health workers in Ezhou to return to work to combat the new outbreak.

The call was followed by a succession of responses. Chen Huaqiao, deputy director of Ezhou's Health Commission, told CCTV on February 6 that 97 people had signed up for the volunteer team, including 39 doctors, 49 nurses, seven technicians and two managers.

About a third of the volunteers are local Ezhou residents, while the rest are from other parts of the country, Chen said. Some of them are on duty on the same day, some on alternate days, and some are still on standby for work in medical and medical isolation observation points. On the afternoon of February 8, a reporter from the Hsinking daily also learned from the Second Ezhou Hospital that volunteers had come to the hospital to support the "war epidemic" .

A couple of old men from Ezhou came back for help. On a train from Nanchang to Beijing West Station on the evening of February 7, an elderly couple found the conductor and hoped to stop at Ezhou, according to the official Weibo account of the Ezhou City Government.

The couple, a retired and soon-to-be retired doctor from Ezhou's Central Hospital, saw the proposal and headed home from their son's home in Liuzhou. During the outbreak, the two elderly train stop at Ezhou Station, no passenger transport and landing procedures, through the train and coordination with higher authorities, the two elderly finally February 7 at 10 pm, lugging luggage from Ezhou Station.

In addition, medical forces from all over the country have been reinforcing Ezhou.

According to public information, a 137-member medical team from Guizhou Province arrived in Ezhou on January 28. A 20-member team of medical experts from Peking University International Hospital also arrived on February 7.

Sixteen provinces will support cities outside Wuhan, with Guangdong Supporting Ezhou, according to the State Council's Joint Prevention and Control Mechanism press conference on February 7. Ezhou Control and Prevention Headquarters said on the 8th, the project is starting.

According to local media in Jiangmen, Guangdong Province, Jiangmen's first aid team of 15 medical staff left for Ezhou on February 9. The team consists of five physicians and 10 nurses, aged 44 and 26, from the Xinhui District People's Hospital in Jiangmen.

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
Leishan Hospital Phase I renovation project completed, February 8, Ezhou version of the "Xiaotangshan" hospital was officially delivered, 50 wards can accommodate 100 patients. Photograph: Ezhou City Hall

Ezhou's Xiaotangshan Hospital to deliver 100 new beds

With support from all sides, the "war epidemic" in Ezhou remains grave.

On February 8, the new Ezhou Headquarters for the prevention and control of pneumonia announced that Ezhou had expanded its nucleic acid testing target, to the city's fever outpatient clinic patients, concentrated on the views of patients to carry out nucleic acid testing, is expected from February 7, the number of confirmed cases in Ezhou will increase. "please understand. "

While the number of confirmed cases has increased, Ezhou has also sought to increase the number of beds.

Ezhou Prevention and Control Command medical team on February 7, said that at present, Ezhou to implement expert inspection diagnosis, if patients need to be hospitalized, through the local hospital to apply for diagnosis, confirmed hospitalization.

The first phase of Ezhou's Xiaotangshan Hospital, or Leishan Hospital, funded by the Ezhou Government, was completed on February 6, with an additional 100 beds for confirmed patients, according to public reports. The medical unit of the Ezhou Prevention and Control Command said that the hospital had been delivered and was arranging for medical staff to be posted on the Ezhou Public Announcement Platform during the official opening hours.

In addition to additional beds for confirmed patients, Ezhou has also placed a number of medical focus on the views, and gradually isolated new crown pneumonia suspected patients.

Ezhou has requisitioned nine units, including student apartments at the Communist Party School, Donghe Hotel, Dongfang Hotel and Ezhou's Renjian Hospital, as the first batch of people with fever to focus on their medical views, the city government said on its website on February 7.

In addition, on February 8,88 wards of the Huarong District Huarong District version of "Little Tangshan" hospital were put into operation, including 62 isolation observation wards and 9 isolation treatment inpatient wards.

Community Prevention and control: Special People in the community to buy food and deliver vegetables, epidemic transparent block rumors

Around the Lunar New Year's Eve, Lin Bin Recalls, the epidemic in Wuhan got so bad that he began to worry about Ezhou.

Ezhou is close to Wuhan, where many Ezhou people study or work, and Wuhan is directly accessible by subway and bus. Lin Bin's family has several cousins, cousins in Wuhan, the unit asked who had contact with the Wuhan people, "basically have. "

After Wuhan closed the station on January 23, Ezhou also closed it. Starting from 1200 hours on 4 February, travel control will be implemented in Ezhou. Each household will be allowed to send one person out every two days. Lin Bin's neighborhood gave each family a card to check in and out. Before, there are neighbors to go out, now the basic people stay at home, no one on the road, no car. The community is also set up to buy vegetables wechat group, there will be a dedicated person to buy vegetables downstairs, residents will also help staff to buy medicine. After a period of tight supply of masks, now the residents' committee sends masks and alcohol to every family, which makes Lin Bin feel that life has been enriched. "The security of life has not been greatly affected. "

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
Ezhou's Sanitation Department disinfects the area around the Ynhwasan Hospital of Traditional Chinese medicine on Feb. 9. Source: Ezhou City Government's official microblog

Lin Bin also believes there is transparency about what's going on in Ezhou. He said it was disturbing that Ezhou had not previously released details of confirmed cases. Now, the case will be announced in detail where the community and building number, and in the community. "It's reassuring to not have rumors flying around and causing unnecessary panic. "

Wang Ling, 26, has his own take on the state of Ezhou. She works in Shanghai and will return to her hometown in Ezhou for the Spring Festival this year. Now that Ezhou has sealed off the city, she can only stay in Ezhou. Every day she stayed at home, outside the city, everywhere in the "war epidemic. ".

Wang Ling says she's never seen Ezhou so quiet. A few days ago, she saw an online anti-epidemic video in Ezhou, the video, familiar with the Ezhou Street scene appeared in front of her. In the evening, the streets of Ezhou are empty. The Sun shines through the clouds. Tall buildings are reflected in the water.

In that video, the commentary says that Ezhou is a "tiny city" so small that few people would notice it on a map of the province. After the outbreak, the bustling streets of Nanpu road were silent, and the traffic jam on Wuchang Avenue was nowhere to be seen.

"I miss the streets and the night scenes in Ezhou, where excitement is the norm, " Wang Ling said. "The start of spring is over. I hope everything will be all right. Go Ezhou. "
